        "id": "note_image_models",
        "type": "utility.note",
        "position": {
          "x": -500,
          "y": 20
        },
        "fields": {
          "body": "### Image model starter\n\nA quick reference workflow for the main image models. Each lane has its own group, preview node, and save node.\n\n- GPT Image 2 text to image creates an image from a prompt only. \n- GPT Image 2 image to image edits one or more source images. \n- Nano Banana 2 is a fast option for image generation or image editing. \n- Nano Banana Pro is the higher-end Nano Banana option for generation or editing. \n\nRight-click a group title to enable or mute the list of nodes. Muted nodes cannot be executed during the run this allows you to only run that set of nodes.\n\nImage-to-image lanes need a source image selected in the Load Image node before running.\n\nHelpful links:\n\n- [Star Media Studio on GitHub](https://github.com/gateway/media-studio)\n- [GitHub issues](https://github.com/gateway/media-studio/issues)\n- [Model credits](https://kie.ai?ref=e7565cf24a7fad4586341a87eaf21e42) \n- [Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/dreamingcomputers/)\n"
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": {
            "width": 460,
            "height": 760
          },
          "ui": {
            "collapsed": false,
            "advancedExpanded": false,
            "accentColor": "#73a7ff",
            "nodeColor": "#151d2b",
            "nodeHeaderColor": "#1d2a3c",
            "customTitle": "Guide"
          },
          "execution": {
            "mode": "enabled",
            "cached_run_id": null,
            "cached_artifact_ids": {}
          }
        }
      },
